                  </hi>. I produce a certificate of the prisoner's con<lb></lb>viction—(<hi rend="italic">read: Newington Sessions, May</hi>, 1855, <hi rend="italic">Susan Hawkins, con<lb></lb>victed of stealing a purse and</hi> 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 7<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Confined four months"</hi>)—Grant is the person—I had her in custody.</p>
